{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/text\/foregroundstyle(_:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"foregroundStyle"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"style"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"S"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","text":"ShapeStyle","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"style","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The color or pattern to use when filling in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground elements. To indicate a specific value, use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/image(_:sourceRect:scale:)"},{"text":", or one of the gradient","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"types, like","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". To set a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style that’s relative to the containing view’s style, use one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"semantic styles, like "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/primary","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view that uses the given foreground style."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to style","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"foreground content like text, shapes, and template images","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(including symbols):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["HStack {","    Image(systemName: \"triangle.fill\")","    Text(\"Hello, world!\")","    RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","        .frame(width: 40, height: 20)","}",".foregroundStyle(.teal)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example above creates a row of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"elements:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use any style that conforms to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/teal","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" color in the example above, or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle\/linearGradient(colors:startPoint:endPoint:)"},{"type":"text","text":" gradient"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown below:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Text(\"Gradient Text\")","    .font(.largeTitle)","    .foregroundStyle(","        .linearGradient(","            colors: [.yellow, .blue],","            startPoint: .top,","            endPoint: .bottom","        )","    )"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Tip","style":"tip","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to fill a single "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape"},{"type":"text","text":" instance with a style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Shape\/fill(style:)"},{"type":"text","text":" shape modifier instead because it’s more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"efficient."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OpenSwiftUI creates a context-dependent render for a given style."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"type":"text","text":" that you load from an asset catalog"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can have different light and dark appearances, while some styles"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also vary by platform."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hierarchical foreground styles like "},{"code":"ShapeStyle\/secondary","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t impose a style of their own, but instead modify other styles."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In particular, they modify the primary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"level of the current foreground style to the degree given by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the hierarchical style’s name."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To find the current foreground style to modify, OpenSwiftUI looks for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the innermost containing style that you apply with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"foregroundStyle(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"code":"View\/foregroundColor(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you haven’t specified a style, OpenSwiftUI uses the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style, as in the following example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you add a foreground style on the enclosing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack"},{"text":", the hierarchical styling responds accordingly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["VStack(alignment: .leading) {","    Label(\"Primary\", systemImage: \"1.square.fill\")","    Label(\"Secondary\", systemImage: \"2.square.fill\")","        .foregroundStyle(.secondary)","}",".foregroundStyle(.blue)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you apply a custom style to a view, the view disables the vibrancy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"effect for foreground elements in that view, or in any of its child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views, that it would otherwise gain from adding a background material"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"— for example, using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View\/background(_:ignoresSafeAreaEdges:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifier. However, hierarchical styles applied to the default foreground"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"don’t disable vibrancy."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"foregroundStyle","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"fileName":"ForegroundStyleModifier.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/ShapeStyle\/ForegroundStyleModifier.swift#L112"},"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"iOS"},{"introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"macOS"},{"introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"tvOS"},{"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"deprecated":false,"name":"watchOS"}],"modules":[{"relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"],"name":"OpenSwiftUI"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE15foregroundStyleyQrqd__AA05ShapeF0Rd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:1